Sentencas: The perovskite Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF) is investigated as the cathode material used in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A Study on Synthesis and Characterization of Dy-Doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ via the Coprecipitation Method

Sentencas: In the present study, La0.6-xDyxSr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (x = 0, 0.3, 0.6) was synthesized through the coprecipitation method.
Titulo: A Study on Synthesis and Characterization of Dy-Doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ via the Coprecipitation Method

Sentencas: The obtained precipitate was calcined at 500, 700, 900, and 1000 degrees C. Phase characterization of the synthesized LSCF and LDySCF powder before and after heat treatment at 700 degrees C was carried out by X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis.
Titulo: A Study on Synthesis and Characterization of Dy-Doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ via the Coprecipitation Method

Sentencas: XRD patterns revealed that the perovskite phase was obtained at 700 degrees C in all calcined samples.

Sentencas: Chemical bond study to investigate the synthesis process was conducted using the Fourier transform infrared spectroscopy technique.
